<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="312" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Preta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Preta</taxonomicName>
Distant, 1908: 234.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="312" type="type-species">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Type-species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Preta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Preta gratiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Melichar, 1903).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="312" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">
Head (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–14" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 14. Habitus photographs. 2, 3 Chouious tianzeus, dorsal and lateral 4 - 6 Phlogis sp. from Malaysia, dorsal and details of head lateral and face 7 Phlogis sp. from Thailand, lateral 8, 9 Preta gratiosa, dorsal and lateral 10 - 12 Signoretia delicata sp. n., detail of head, dorsal, lateral, and frontal 13, 14 Signoretia kintendela sp. n., dorsal and lateral." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/24488" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) strongly and angulately produced. Pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–14" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 14. Habitus photographs. 2, 3 Chouious tianzeus, dorsal and lateral 4 - 6 Phlogis sp. from Malaysia, dorsal and details of head lateral and face 7 Phlogis sp. from Thailand, lateral 8, 9 Preta gratiosa, dorsal and lateral 10 - 12 Signoretia delicata sp. n., detail of head, dorsal, lateral, and frontal 13, 14 Signoretia kintendela sp. n., dorsal and lateral." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/24488" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) with pair of well-developed submedial longitudinal carinae extended entire length. Forewings (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 15–20" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 15 - 20. Fore- and hindwing. 15, 16 Phlogis sp. from Thailand. 17, 18 Preta gratiosa. 19, 20 Signoretia aureola." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/24490" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) with claval veins fused for short distance near midlength.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="312" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Preta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Preta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Oriental region and currently includes two species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Preta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Preta gratiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Preta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Preta luzonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baker, 1923, the latter known only from the Philippines. It can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Signoretia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its complete paired longitudinal carinae on the pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–14" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 14. Habitus photographs. 2, 3 Chouious tianzeus, dorsal and lateral 4 - 6 Phlogis sp. from Malaysia, dorsal and details of head lateral and face 7 Phlogis sp. from Thailand, lateral 8, 9 Preta gratiosa, dorsal and lateral 10 - 12 Signoretia delicata sp. n., detail of head, dorsal, lateral, and frontal 13, 14 Signoretia kintendela sp. n., dorsal and lateral." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/24488" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and medially fused claval veins of forewings (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 15–20" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 15 - 20. Fore- and hindwing. 15, 16 Phlogis sp. from Thailand. 17, 18 Preta gratiosa. 19, 20 Signoretia aureola." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/24490" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), as indicated in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="312" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="312">
Indonesia (Sumbawa, Jacobi 1941 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">apud</emphasis>
Knight 2010), E. and W. Malaysia (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, CF" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Journal of Science" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" pagination="34 - 405" refId="B3" refString="Baker, CF, 1923. The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species. Philippine Journal of Science 23: 34 - 405" title="The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species." volume="23" year="1923">Baker 1923</bibRefCitation>
), Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, WL" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" refId="B7" refString="Distant, WL, 1908. Rhynchota-Homoptera and appendix (pt), The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 501 pp." title="Rhynchota-Homoptera and appendix (pt), The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma." year="1908">Distant 1908</bibRefCitation>
), Philippines (Luzon, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, CF" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Journal of Science" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" pagination="34 - 405" refId="B3" refString="Baker, CF, 1923. The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species. Philippine Journal of Science 23: 34 - 405" title="The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species." volume="23" year="1923">Baker 1923</bibRefCitation>
), Singapore (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, CF" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Journal of Science" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" pagination="34 - 405" refId="B3" refString="Baker, CF, 1923. The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species. Philippine Journal of Science 23: 34 - 405" title="The Jassoidea related to the Stenocotidae with special reference to Malayan species." volume="23" year="1923">Baker 1923</bibRefCitation>
), Sri Lanka (
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar, L" journalOrPublisher="Felix L. Dames, Berlin" pageId="19" pageNumber="322" refId="B14" refString="Melichar, L, 1903. Homopteren-Fauna von Ceylon. Felix L. Dames, Berlin, 248 pp." title="Homopteren-Fauna von Ceylon." year="1903">Melichar 1903</bibRefCitation>
), and Thailand [
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="312">new record</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
